│                                                                               │
│ ## Initial Observations ##                                                    │
│                                                                               │
│ The reproducer is already minimized. Based on my experience in debugging      │
│ these bugs, the issue is likely introduced by the *first transformation*, or  │
│ due to incorrect analysis information feeding into it.                        │
│ Here, the *first transformation* means the *first transformation point* that  │
│ modifies the IR in the pass regardless of whether it's in the                 │
│ `nary-reassociate` module or other modules.                                   │
│ #### Opt Information ####                                                     │
│                                                                               │
│ To gather more insight, I ran `opt` to inspect both the transformations and   │
│ the analysis results. Below are the command and the resulting log:            │
│                                                                               │
│ ```bash                                                                       │
│ $ bin/opt -disable-output --passes=print<scalar-evolution>,nary-reassociate   │
│ --scalar-evolution-use-expensive-range-sharpening                             │
│ --debug-only=scalar-evolution /tmp/reprod_q2o673nv.ll                         │
│ Printing analysis 'Scalar Evolution Analysis' for function 'f':               │
│ Classifying expressions for: @f                                               │
│   %2 = phi i32 [ %3, %bb2 ], [ 0, %bb ], [ 0, %1 ]                            │
│   -->  {0,+,1}<nuw><nsw><%bb1> U:                                             │
│ ```                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ From this log, I identified the first transformation point as:                │
│                                                                               │
│ ```                                                                           │
│ llvm/include/llvm/IR/Value.h::llvm::Value::getValueID()                       │
│ ```                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Here is the relevant backtrace at the moment of the transformation:           │
│                                                                               │
│ ```stack                                                                      │
│ (frame 0) llvm/include/llvm/IR/Value.h:532 in llvm::Value::getValueID         │
│ (frame 1) llvm/include/llvm/IR/Value.h:1025 in                                │
│ llvm::isa_impl<llvm::GlobalVariable, llvm::Value, void>::doit                 │
│ (frame 6) llvm/include/llvm/IR/Value.h:1049 in                                │
│ llvm::isa_impl<llvm::GlobalObject, llvm::Value, void>::doit                   │
│ (frame 11) llvm/include/llvm/IR/Value.h:1043 in                               │
│ llvm::isa_impl<llvm::GlobalValue, llvm::Value, void>::doit                    │
│ (frame 18) llvm/lib/IR/Value.cpp:458 in                                       │
│ llvm::Value::assertModuleIsMaterializedImpl                                   │
│ (frame 19) llvm/include/llvm/IR/Value.h:340 in                                │
│ llvm::Value::assertModuleIsMaterialized                                       │
│ (frame 20) llvm/include/llvm/IR/Value.h:402 in llvm::Value::user_begin        │
│ (frame 21) llvm/include/llvm/IR/CFG.h:67 in                                   │
