│   9 // The ScalarEvolution class is an LLVM pass which can be used to analyze │
│ and                                                                           │
│  10 // categorize scalar expressions in loops.  It specializes in recognizing │
│  11 // general induction variables, representing them with the abstract and   │
│ opaque                                                                        │
│  12 // SCEV class.  Given this analysis, trip counts of loops and other       │
│ important                                                                     │
│  13 // properties can be obtained.                                            │
│  14 //                                                                        │
│  15 // This analysis is primarily useful for induction variable substitution  │
│ and                                                                           │
│  16 // strength reduction.                                                    │
│  17 //                                                                        │
│  18                                                                           │
